This paper is about image recognition using deep learning, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of larger deep neural network models and novel data augmentation approaches, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a custom-built supercomputer and optimized parallel algorithm, which are topics in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of multi-scale high-resolution images, which is a topic in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
